<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,153,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A." box="[322,501,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" pagination="251 - 255" refId="ref6293" refString="Mocsary, A. (1899) Species novae generis Centris Fabr. in collectione Musaei Nationalis Hungarici. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 22, 251 - 255." type="journal article" year="1899">Mocsáry (1899)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention how many female specimens he used to describe the species. A single female with original labels was found at 
<collectionCode box="[640,726,189,215]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">HNHM</collectionCode>
being designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[994,1100,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: Brasilia [printed] Piauchy [handwritten]\ [light greenish square] 82 [handwritten]\ [black-rimmed] 848 100. [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1899" box="[425,534,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornuta">
<emphasis box="[425,534,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">bicornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mocs [handwritten] det. 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[817,950,261,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" pagination="427 - 431" refId="ref5980" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">Friese 1898</bibRefCitation>
[printed]. According to the accession book at 
<collectionCode box="[178,266,297,323]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">HNHM</collectionCode>
, this specimen was purchased from the insect dealer Eduard Menkl in 1889.
</paragraph>
